# GitLab Bud Chart - Code Owners
# This file defines who owns and should review code in different parts of the repository
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Global owners (will be requested for review on all PRs)
* @your-username

# Backend code
/backend/ @your-username @backend-team
/backend/app/ @your-username @backend-team
/backend/tests/ @your-username @backend-team @qa-team

# Frontend code  
/frontend/ @your-username @frontend-team
/frontend/src/ @your-username @frontend-team
/frontend/tests/ @your-username @frontend-team @qa-team

# Documentation
/docs/ @your-username @docs-team
*.md @your-username @docs-team

# Configuration and deployment
/.github/ @your-username @devops-team
/scripts/ @your-username @devops-team
docker* @your-username @devops-team
*.yml @your-username @devops-team
*.yaml @your-username @devops-team

# Security-sensitive files
.env.example @your-username @security-team
.gitignore @your-username @security-team

# Dependencies
package*.json @your-username @security-team
requirements.txt @your-username @security-team
pyproject.toml @your-username @security-team